      <column>
        <label>
          <text>   </text>
        </label>
        <label>
          <text>Must have JMRI 3.9.5 or later.</text>
          <text xml:lang="it">Dovete avere JMRI 3.9.5 o successivo.</text>
        </label>
		<group>
			<qualifier>
				<variableref>First</variableref>
				<relation>exists</relation>
				<value>1</value>
				</qualifier>
			<label>
			  <text>   </text>
			</label>
			<row>
				<display item="First" format="radiobuttons"/>
			</row>
			<label>
			  <text>   </text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>&lt;html&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To use the "Default Whistle/Horn" setting and the rotate whistle/horn function (default on F9):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>For each function to have a whistle/horn assigned to it, select only the first choice, as listed above, of that group (long, short, quill, for, rev or stop)</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>i.e. for a long whistle select "Whistle Alamo Michigan Plant Long"</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>Note: With this config only one whistle/horn can be configured at a time</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>   </text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>&lt;html&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To have different whistles/horns on different functions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>Set "Default Whistle/Horn" to first choice as listed above</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>For each function, select the desired whistle/horn name from the desired group (long, short, quill, for, rev or stop)</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>Do not use the rotate whistle/horn function, to prevent accidental changes, remap F9 to something else and do not have rotate whistle/horn mapped to anything</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>example: F2 to "Southern Pacific Daylight #4460 6 chime long" and F3 to "Leslie 200 long"</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>Note: With this config, use of rotate whistle/horn function will cause spoken whistle/horn name not to match played whistle/horn sound</text>
			</label>
			<label>
			  <text>Also automatic Forward, Reverse and Stop toots will not play correct whistle/horn, they will play correct sound if mapped to functions</text>
			</label>
		</group>
		<label>
          <text>   </text>
        </label>
		<row>
			<display item="Sound Option 1" />
		</row>
		<group>
